N}'(f|_{_{S^2}})||_N=0$,\nwere $\\text{Sym}^N(\\mathbb{C}^2)$ denotes the symmetric subspace of\n$(\\mathbb{C}^2)^{N \\otimes}$. Finally, we give an application regarding the\n(quantum) Curie-Weiss model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 9 May 2020 12:03:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Sep 2020 14:37:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Sep 2020 06:47:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-13"}
